ca.uhn.fhir.parser

Interface IJsonLikeParser

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IParser
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    JsonParser

    public interface IJsonLikeParser
extends IParser
    An extension to the parser interface that is implemented by parsers that understand a generalized form of JSON data. This generalized form uses Map-like, List-like, and scalar elements to construct resources.

    Thread safety: Parsers are not guaranteed to be thread safe. Create a new parser instance for every thread or every message being parsed/encoded.

        Parse a DSTU1 style Atom Bundle. Note that as of DSTU2, Bundle is a resource so you should use parseResource(Class, JsonLikeStructure) with the Bundle class found in the ca.uhn.hapi.fhir.model.[version].resource package instead.

        Parses a resource from a JSON-like data structure
        Parameters:
        theResourceType - The resource type to use. This can be used to explicitly specify a class which extends a built-in type (e.g. a custom type extending the default Patient class)
